e business slogans now heard around the globe are being adopted in this set of organizations renowned for its strongly held internal values, such as participatory democracy, solidarity, and equality. Instead of emphasizing the special or unique qualities of the Mondragón experience, this book demonstrates the case's relevance to trends in all sectors and across the industrialized world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2019) 0aManagementxEmployee participationzSpainzMondragón. 0aProducer cooperativeszSpainzMondragón. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066750940uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501721113423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501721113.jpg  a978-3-11-066750-9  COR eBook-Package 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA15STM  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA3STM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG